In this I think that ifPresent would not help us because I need to return the optional value. I thought about chaining all optional calls, but I think the code would be more unclear. The If's sequence is helpful to expose what would be the order to load stuff:

No modelId is provided, so we try to return the only one that is registered;
Next we try to load some existing file with the given model Id;
Finally we try to load external files (only if it is enabled to load external files)

if we do not allow multiple imports than we simple return the single one that is potentially loaded.

